                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/36: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Greece (<persName type="to">Morris</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-01T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 1, 1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. Ratifications of extradition treaty United States and Greece were exchanged
                    with Greek Minister today. You will promptly so inform appropriate authorities
                    and renew request you were directed to make in Department’s 49, October 10, 11
                    a.m. for provisional arrest and detention of Samuel Insull, Sr. with a view to
                    his extradition on the charges of embezzlement and larceny upon which warrants
                    of arrest have been issued in Cook County, Illinois.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
